# brew-autosign packages.conf
#
# Lists Homebrew packages whose binaries should be auto-signed with the local
# code-signing identity after every `brew upgrade`, so that macOS Keychain ACLs
# stay valid across upgrades.
#
# ─── Syntax ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# One entry per line. Two forms are supported:
#
#   <package>
#       Sign every UNSIGNED Mach-O executable found in
#           <brew-prefix>/Cellar/<package>/<version>/bin/
#       (Already-signed binaries — by Apple, the vendor, or by us — are left
#       alone; see "Safety" below.)
#
#   <package>:<binary1>,<binary2>,...
#       Sign only the explicitly listed binaries inside the package's bin/
#       directory. Useful when a package ships many tools and you only need
#       a subset re-signed.
#
# Whitespace is ignored. Comments start with `#`. Blank lines are ignored.
#
# ─── Fields ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   <package>   — the exact Homebrew formula name as installed (matches the
#                 directory under Cellar/). For tap-installed formulae use the
#                 unqualified leaf name (e.g. `fnox`, not `user/tap/fnox`).
#   <binary>    — the file name inside the package's bin/ directory.
#
# ─── Safety ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The automatic agent pass never overwrites an existing signature. Each binary
# is classified as:
#   - signed by us           → skipped (idempotent)
#   - signed by someone else → skipped (Apple / vendor signature preserved)
#   - not signed at all      → signed with the active identity
# (An explicit `brew-autosign sign --force` re-signs configured binaries even if
# already signed — used when switching identities. It only touches packages
# listed here, never arbitrary files.)
#
# ─── Signing identity ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Packages here are signed with brew-autosign's active identity — a managed
# self-signed cert by default. To sign with your own Apple Development /
# Developer ID cert instead (auto-detected from your keychain):
#   brew-autosign identity list
#   brew-autosign identity set <name>
# The identity lives separately in ~/.config/brew-autosign/identity.
#
# ─── After editing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Run:
#   brew-autosign reload
# to regenerate the LaunchAgent's WatchPaths from the new list.
#
# ─── Examples ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment to enable.

# fnox                      # secret manager — needs stable signature for keychain ACLs
# yubikey-agent             # any unsigned tool you trust enough to local-sign

# Restrict to specific binaries when a package ships many tools:
# my-pkg:cli,daemon
